---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ChapterNav from "../components/ChapterNav.astro";
---

<Layout title="Load Testing with Artillery - SYP">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a
            href="/syp-overview"
            class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to SYP Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1
                    class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white"
                >
                    Load Testing with Artillery
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Performance testing: identifying bottlenecks, validating
                    capacity, and optimizing under realistic load
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Unit tests verify correctness, but integration tests
                        verify behavior. Artillery goes a step further: it
                        verifies performance under load. I created realistic
                        load test scenarios to simulate hundreds of concurrent
                        users to find bottlenecks, validate capacity, and ensure
                        the system degrades gracefully under stress.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Learning Journey
                    </h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                ⚡ Challenge: Realistic Scenarios
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Not all users behave the same. Some create
                                users, others bid on items, others search.
                                Created multiple scenarios with different user
                                flows to simulate realistic traffic patterns.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                📈 Challenge: Load Phases
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Load testing isn't just "100 req/s". Implemented
                                warm-up phase (gradual ramp), peak phase
                                (constant max load), and cool-down phase
                                (gradual reduction) to simulate real-world
                                traffic patterns.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🔍 Challenge: Identifying Bottlenecks
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Some endpoints are slow under load, others fast.
                                Used Artillery to measure response times,
                                identify slow queries, and find resource
                                contention.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🛠️ Challenge: Optimization
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                After identifying slow endpoints, implemented
                                fixes: added database indexes, implemented
                                caching, used pagination more efficiently, and
                                optimized N+1 queries.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                ✅ Key Learning
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Load testing is how we find problems at scale.
                                Artillery makes it easy to simulate thousands of
                                concurrent users without complex infrastructure.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Key Implementation
                    </h2>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            User Creation & Registration Load Test
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`# UserLoadTest.yaml - Artillery Scenario
config:
  target: "http://localhost:8080"
  phases:
    # Warm-up: Gradually increase load from 1 to 20 req/s over 40 seconds
    - duration: 40
      arrivalRate: 1
      rampTo: 20
      name: "Warm up"
    
    # Peak: Hold at 20-50 req/s for 10 seconds
    - duration: 10
      arrivalRate: 20
      rampTo: 50
      name: "Peak load"
    
    # Cool-down: Gradually decrease from 50 to 1 req/s over 40 seconds
    - duration: 40
      arrivalRate: 50
      rampTo: 1
      name: "Cool down"

  # Processor for custom logic
  processor: "./LoadTestFunctions.js"
  
  # Timeout settings
  timeout: 10
  http:
    timeout: 10

scenarios:
  - name: "User Registration Flow"
    weight: 100
    flow:
      # Step 1: Register user
      - post:
          url: "/api/users/register"
          json:
            firstName: "{{ firstName }}"
            lastName: "{{ lastName }}"
            email: "{{ email }}"
            password: "{{ password }}"
          beforeRequest: "generateUserData"  # Custom function
          expect:
            - statusCode: 201
          capture:
            - json: "$.data.id"
              as: "userId"
      
      # Step 2: Login user
      - post:
          url: "/api/auth/login"
          json:
            email: "{{ email }}"
            password: "{{ password }}"
          expect:
            - statusCode: 200
          capture:
            - json: "$.data.token"
              as: "token"
      
      # Step 3: Get user profile
      - get:
          url: "/api/users/{{ userId }}"
          headers:
            Authorization: "Bearer {{ token }}"
          expect:
            - statusCode: 200`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Three phases: warm-up (1→20 req/s), peak (20→50
                            req/s), cool-down (50→1 req/s). Each phase realistic
                            and identifiable.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Item Bidding Load Test
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`# ItemBiddingTest.yaml - Complex Bidding Scenario
scenarios:
  - name: "Item Search & Bidding"
    weight: 50
    flow:
      # Step 1: Search items with pagination
      - get:
          url: "/api/items?page={{ page }}&size=20&sort=createdAt&direction=DESC"
          expect:
            - statusCode: 200
          capture:
            - json: "$.data.content[0].id"
              as: "itemId"

      # Step 2: Get item details
      - get:
          url: "/api/items/{{ itemId }}"
          expect:
            - statusCode: 200
          capture:
            - json: "$.data.currentBid"
              as: "currentBid"

      # Step 3: Place bid
      - post:
          url: "/api/items/{{ itemId }}/bid"
          headers:
            Authorization: "Bearer {{ token }}"
          json:
            amount: "{{ bidAmount }}"  # Must be > currentBid
          expect:
            - statusCode: 201
          beforeRequest: "generateValidBid"

      # Step 4: View bid history
      - get:
          url: "/api/items/{{ itemId }}/bids?page=0&size=10"
          expect:
            - statusCode: 200

config:
  phases:
    - duration: 30
      arrivalRate: 5
      rampTo: 30
      name: "Warm up"
    
    - duration: 20
      arrivalRate: 30
      rampTo: 100
      name: "Peak"
    
    - duration: 30
      arrivalRate: 100
      rampTo: 5
      name: "Cool down"`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Realistic user flow: search, view details, bid,
                            check history. Tests pagination, bid validation,
                            complex queries.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Load Test Helper Functions
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// LoadTestFunctions.js - Custom Logic
module.exports = {
  generateUserData: generateUserData,
  generateValidBid: generateValidBid,
  generateItemData: generateItemData,
  checkStatusCode: checkStatusCode,
  randomPage: randomPage,
  indexArray: indexArray
};

// Generate unique user data for each request
function generateUserData(context, ee, next) {
  context.vars.email = "user" + Math.random() * 1000000 + "@test.com";
  context.vars.firstName = "Test" + Math.random() * 1000000;
  context.vars.lastName = "User";
  context.vars.password = "SecurePassword123!";
  return next();
}

// Ensure bid is higher than current bid
function generateValidBid(context, ee, next) {
  const currentBid = parseFloat(context.vars.currentBid) || 0;
  context.vars.bidAmount = (currentBid + 10).toFixed(2);
  console.log("Placing bid: " + context.vars.bidAmount);
  return next();
}

// Generate item data
function generateItemData(context, ee, next) {
  context.vars.itemName = "Item #" + Math.random() * 1000000;
  context.vars.description = "Test item";
  context.vars.startingBid = "50.00";
  return next();
}

// Custom response handler
function checkStatusCode(context, ee, next) {
  if (context.statusCode !== 200) {
    console.log("Status code: " + context.statusCode);
  }
  return next();
}

// Random pagination
function randomPage(context, ee, next) {
  context.vars.page = Math.floor(Math.random() * 10);
  return next();
}

// Array index helper
function indexArray(context, ee, next) {
  context.vars.index = context.vars.$loopIndex || 0;
  return next();
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Custom JavaScript functions inject realistic data:
                            random emails, progressive bid amounts, random
                            pagination.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Test Results & Metrics
                    </h2>
                    <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-300">
                        <div
                            class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30"
                        >
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">
                                📊 Key Metrics
                            </h3>
                            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Throughput:</strong> Requests per second
                                    the system can handle
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Response Times:</strong> p50 (median),
                                    p95, p99 percentiles
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Error Rate:</strong> % of requests that
                                    fail under load
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Ramp Success:</strong> Can system handle
                                    gradual increase?
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Graceful Degradation:</strong> Does it
                                    reject gracefully or crash?
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div
                            class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30"
                        >
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">
                                📈 Example Results
                            </h3>
                            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>
                                    • User Registration: p95 = 250ms at 50 req/s
                                    ✓
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    • Item Search: p95 = 180ms at 100 req/s ✓
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    • Bid Placement: p95 = 320ms at 50 req/s ✓
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    • Error Rate at peak: 0.2% (database
                                    connection timeouts)
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div
                            class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30"
                        >
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">
                                🔧 Optimizations Applied
                            </h3>
                            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>
                                    • Added database index on itemId for bid
                                    queries
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    • Implemented pagination defaults (max 100
                                    items per page)
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    • Optimized N+1 queries with eager loading
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    • Increased connection pool from 10 to 20
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Running Load Tests
                    </h2>
                    <div
                        class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                    >
                        <pre
                            class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`# Install Artillery
npm install -g artillery

# Run a load test
artillery run UserLoadTest.yaml

# Run and generate report
artillery run UserLoadTest.yaml --output results.json
artillery report results.json --output report.html

# Run from a specific directory
cd tests/load-tests
artillery run ItemBiddingTest.yaml

# View detailed output
artillery run UserLoadTest.yaml -v

# Run for a specific duration
artillery run UserLoadTest.yaml --duration 120

# Output: Console and HTML Reports
> Summary report @ 12:34:56 UTC
  Scenarios launched:  3600
  Scenarios completed: 3599
  Requests completed:  14396
  RPS sent: 59.9
  Request latency [ms]:
    min: 5
    max: 1250
    median: 145
    p95: 320
    p99: 480
  Scenario success rate: 99.97%
  Scenario counts: ... ✓`}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Technology Stack
                    </h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {
                            [
                                "Artillery",
                                "YAML Scenarios",
                                "JavaScript Functions",
                                "Load Phases",
                                "Response Metrics",
                                "HTML Reports",
                            ].map((tech) => (
                                <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                    {tech}
                                </span>
                            ))
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Results & Impact
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Identified Bottlenecks:</strong> Found slow
                                queries before users complained</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Validated Capacity:</strong> System handles
                                expected peak load with acceptable latency</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Continuous Testing:</strong> Load tests run
                                in CI/CD to prevent performance regressions</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Realistic Scenarios:</strong> Tests simulate
                                actual user behavior, not just HTTP noise</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Confidence in Scale:</strong> Know system
                                handles growth without panic</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
            <ChapterNav
                prevLink="/syp-integration-testing"
                prevText="Integration Testing"
                nextLink="/syp-overview"
                nextText="Back to Overview"
            />
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
